* ''XDM X-Treme Dungeon Mastery'' (illustrations, written by [[Tracy Hickman]] and [[Curtis Hickman]]), ISBN 0977907465, July 20, 2009, The Tayler Corporation

==Awards==
Tayler won the [[Web Cartoonists' Choice Awards]] Best Cameo Award in 2001, and was also nominated for Best Comic, Best Writing, Best Other Character, and Best Science-Fiction Comic the same year.<ref name="wcca2001">{{cite web|url=http://www.ccawards.com/2001.htm|title=2001 Winners and Nominees|publisher=Web Cartoonist's Choice Awards Committee|date=2001|accessdate=April 21, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5p9IkMRFf|archivedate=April 21, 2010}}</ref> He won WCCA Outstanding Science Fiction Comic in 2004,<ref name="wcca2004">{{cite web|url=http://www.ccawards.com/2004.htm|title=2004 Results|publisher=Web Cartoonist's Choice Awards Committee|date=2004|accessdate=April 21, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5p9J1fGwz|archivedate=April 21, 2010}}</ref> and was nominated for the same award in 2005<ref name="wcca2005">{{cite web|url=http://www.ccawards.com/2005.htm|title=2005 Results|publisher=Web Cartoonist's Choice Awards Committee|date=2005|accessdate=April 21, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5p9JJLQxp|archivedate=April 21, 2010}}</ref> and 2007.<ref name="wcca2007">{{cite web|url=http://www.ccawards.com/2007.htm|title=2007 Results|publisher=Web Cartoonist's Choice Awards Committee|date=2007|accessdate=April 21, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5p9JLT7dk|archivedate=April 21, 2010}}</ref>

He was nominated for a [[Hugo Award]] (Best Graphic Story) for ''Schlock Mercenary'' in 2009 and 2010.<ref name="hugonom2009">{{cite web|url=http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/2009-hugo-awards/|title=2009 Hugo Awards|publisher=[[Worldcon#World Science Fiction Society|World Science Fiction Society]]|date=August 10, 2009|accessdate=April 20, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5p9Kbt4t7|archivedate=April 21, 2010}}</ref><ref name="hugonom2010">{{cite web|url=http://www.thehugoawards.org/2010/04/2010-hugo-award-nominees-details/|title=2010 Hugo Award Nominees <U+2013> Details|publisher=[[World Science Fiction Society]]|date=April 4, 2010|accessdate=April 20, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5p9KgKNe0|archivedate=April 21, 2010}}</ref>  

